  <section>
    <h2>Political Journey</h2>
    <div class="timeline-entry">
      <strong>1987:</strong> Joined Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP).
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-entry">
      <strong>2001:</strong> Became Chief Minister of Gujarat.
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-entry">
      <strong>2014:</strong> Sworn in as the 14th Prime Minister of India.
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-entry">
      <strong>2019:</strong> Re-elected as Prime Minister with a stronger majority.
    </div>
    <div class="image-gallery">
      <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6f/Narendra_Modi_Campaigning.jpg" alt="Modi Campaigning">
